  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, we input the embedding as graph nodes, accompanied by EVCs and RCs (graph edges), into the six graph convolutional layers of the dual stacked GCNs.",
    "These layers, working in conjunction with a block of two fully connected (FC) layers, meticulously process the information from the two GCNs, ultimately generating a tensor of probabilities for assessing the viability of assigning functional annotations to the protein.",
    "In addition, an activation score, derived using the gradientweighted class activation maps (Grad-CAMs) approach 32, is used to assess the significance of each individual residue in a specific function.",
    "The score allows PhiGnet to pinpoint functional sites at the level of individual residues (bottom, Fig. 1c, see Methods).",
    "As an example, we computed RCs for the Serine-aspartate repeatcontaining protein D (SdrD) that promotes bacterial survival in human blood by inhibiting innate immune-mediated bacterial killing 33, 34."
  ],
